# {{ ip }} verification environment

Generated by **uvm-gen {{ gen_version }}** for Cadence Xcelium (xrun, bundled
UVM-1.2). Everything is prefixed `{{ ip }}_` and self-contained for vertical
reuse inside an SoC environment.

## Quick start

```bash
cd sim
make compile                          # compile + elaborate (works before any TODO is filled)
make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test     # smoke: reset + a few transactions, UVM_ERROR 0
make waves TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test   # same, with SHM probing
make regress                          # vManager: launch sim/{{ vsif_name }}
make matrix                           # configuration vs. verification status
```

Select a configuration at run time (one YAML per configuration in `cfg/`):

```bash
make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test CFG=cfg/{{ cfg_relname }}
```

Every run prints a configuration signature banner (config_name, parameters,
param hash) and appends a record to `verif_matrix.yaml`.

## Layout

| Path | Content |
|---|---|
| `cfg/` | configuration YAMLs (one per IP configuration; `extends:` supported) |
| `agents/<name>_agent/` | interface, seq_item, sequencer, driver, monitor, cfg, agent, base seq, package |
| `vip/<name>_vip/` | Cadence VIP wrapper (cfg + agent shell, TODO(vip) markers) |
| `env/` | env_cfg, env, scoreboard, coverage subscribers, virtual sequencer, RAL stub |
| `seq_lib/` | virtual sequences ({{ ip }}_base_vseq, {{ ip }}_smoke_vseq) |
| `tests/` | {{ ip }}_base_test, {{ ip }}_smoke_test, test package |
| `tb/` | {{ ip }}_tb_top + DUT stub |
| `sim/` | Makefile, tb.f, vip_*.f, {{ vsif_name }}, scripts/ |
| `.github/` | Copilot agentic verification kit (instructions + phase prompts) |

## Ground rules

* **One config object**: `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` carries every knob and every
  virtual interface. Components never read the config_db for vifs by path.
* **is_active**: per-interface switch in `{{ ip }}_env_cfg`; passive agents
  build no driver/sequencer. Flip everything passive without code edits:
  `make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test XRUN_OPTS=+{{ IP }}_PASSIVE=all`
* **Re-run policy**: the generator never overwrites existing files. Adding an
  agent/VIP to the YAML and re-running creates only the new files; wire them
  into `env/`, `sim/tb.f`, `tb/` by hand (the generator lists the stale files)
  or use `--force` to regenerate everything.
* **Cadence VIPs**: `$CDN_VIP_ROOT` must point at the VIP install whenever the
  active config requests VIPs; `sim/vip_<protocol>.f` is the single file to
  edit per protocol.

## SoC (vertical) reuse

```systemverilog
// inside the SoC env's build_phase
{{ ip }}_env_cfg ip_cfg = {{ ip }}_env_cfg::type_id::create("ip_cfg");
ip_cfg.set_agent_activity("all", UVM_PASSIVE);  // RTL drives the buses
ip_cfg.env_owns_bus = 0;                        // no RAL adapter/predictor wiring
{% for a in agents %}
ip_cfg.{{ a.name }}_cfg.vif = soc_cfg.{{ ip }}_{{ a.name }}_vif;  // SoC-level signals
{% endfor %}
uvm_config_db#({{ ip }}_env_cfg)::set(this, "m_{{ ip }}_env", "cfg", ip_cfg);
m_{{ ip }}_env = {{ ip }}_env::type_id::create("m_{{ ip }}_env", this);
```

RAL: instantiate `{{ ip }}_reg_block` as a child of the SoC register model
(`default_map.add_submap(ip_regs.default_map, <base>)`), then set
`ip_cfg.regmodel = ip_regs;` — the env skips building its own block, and with
`env_owns_bus = 0` it leaves adapter/predictor wiring to the SoC.

Compilation from an SoC build: `export {{ IP }}_VERIF_HOME=<this dir>` and add
`-f ${{ IP }}_VERIF_HOME/sim/tb.f` (drop `tb/*.sv` from it or exclude the tb
files if the SoC has its own top).

## Copilot agentic flow

`.github/copilot-instructions.md` carries the env conventions;
`.github/prompts/` contains one prompt per verification phase, each stating
its precondition so an agent can chain them:

1. `connect-dut` → 2. `implement-agents` → 3. `write-tests` →
4. `triage-regression` → 5. `coverage-closure` → 6. `verif-closure`

See the repository-level uvm-gen README for the full tool documentation.
